tags.text: module:azure-iot-device.deviceMethod.DeviceMethodRequest

`DeviceMethodRequest` is a class that captures the data
                 passed in from the service when a device method call is
                 made. An instance of this class is passed as the second
                 parameter to the callback registered via the
                 {@link module:azure-iot-device.Client#onDeviceMethod} method.

The request identifier supplied by the
                                   service for this device method call.
The name of the method to be called.

A Node `Buffer` representing the payload
                                   of the method call request.
module:azure-iot-device.deviceMethod.DeviceMethodResponse

`DeviceMethodResponse` provides functionality that allows
                 a device method implementation to construct and send a
                 response back to the service for a device method call. An
                 instance of this class is passed as the second parameter
                 to the callback registered via the
                 {@link module:azure-iot-device.Client#onDeviceMethod} method.
                 method.

The request identifier supplied by the
                                   service for this device method call.

An object that implements the interface
                                   expected of a transport object, e.g.,
                                   {@link module:azure-iot-device~Http|Http}.
module:azure-iot-device.deviceMethod.DeviceMethodResponse#send

Sends the device method's response back to the service via
                   the underlying transport object using the status parameter
                   as the status of the method call.
{ReferenceError}       If the `status` parameter is not a number.

{Error}                If this response has already been sent to the
                               service in a previous call to it. This method
                               should be called only once.

comment.text:
A numeric status code to be sent back to the
                               service.
The payload of the method response.

A callback function which will be
                               called once the response has been sent back to
                               the service. An error object is passed as an
                               argument to the function in case an error
                               occurs.
